    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4367" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρως</span></b> , gen. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρωος</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρω̆ος</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρω̆ι</span> and
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρῳ</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἥρω</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">α</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hero,
            warrior;</span> a title of honor for the free and brave; alone as
          subst., <i><span class="en">Il. 1.4</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.179</span></i>; in address, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.104</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            10.416</span></i>; w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Δαναοί, Ἀχαιοί</span>,
          likewise with single names, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.200</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 2.15</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.163</span></i>; joined w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεράποντες
            Ἄρηος,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 2.110</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            γέρων</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.155</span></i>. Never
          =demigod.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
